This paper is primarily focused on improving the running time bounds for Hamiltonian Monte Carlo (HMC), which is a widely used method in both Statistics and Machine Learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves analyzing the regularity properties of the input data, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
